28/11/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Interior Ministries of Bulgaria and Turkey are expected to seal an agreement on co-operation in anti-terror activities in the coming months, announced the head of the Bulgarian National Service for Fight against Organised Crime, General Valentin Petrov on Friday (26 November).
Following talks between representatives of the security authorities of the two countries in Sofia, he said the Turkish side was particularly interested in Bulgaria's experience in the discovery and prevention of bomb attacks.
(Sega - 27/11/04;
Nova TV - 26/11/04)
